fp|2|cp|2|cs|3|ht|e|at|^b@2Eventhost: In honour of BIL's 12th Birthday Celebration, I would like to welcome Paul Gipson back to the BILies Retreat.
Paul has been a long time favourite and has given much of his time to mentoring and teaching new BIL members.  
Paulg has played bridge for about thirty-five years, starting in a local club and progressing quickly to tournaments. His regular bridge partner is brother Alex with whom he plays in most major UK tournaments 
and the occasional Summer NABC in the USA.  
Paul's favourite bridge memory is playing the Nickell team in the Spingold. 
Paul plays in the English Premier League and has also been the non-playing captain of Scotland Open and Women's teams. He spends a lot of time coaching Scottish international pairs.  Using BBO plays a major 
part to help them prepare for competition, particularly setting practice matches and partnership bidding tables.
Paul, along with wife Helen, lives in the Scottish Borders and enjoys walking his dogs in the beautiful countryside. Helen is one of the world's leading Scrabble players but does play bridge and together they have won county and national mixed pairs events.

Paul says his real aim as a mentor is to help with consistent play. This means discipline in bidding and forming a plan when declaring and defending. He finds that the problem most BIL members have is not a limit to their knowledge but the ability to apply the right bit of knowledge in a timely fashion! 
So he concentrates on teaching players to understand the basics and the inferences that can be taken from a course of action.

@h@h  Let's give a warm BILies welcome to Paul Gipson @h@h

