at|paulg:  One piece of advice I always give BIL players is to take their time at trick 1 when playing the contract .. make a plan before following from dummy... even if there is a singleton there
This is the type of hand where, as kibitzers, we can see how to make lots of tricks
...and we also see that Anne could have gone down if Rosemary had played the @hQ instead of another spade at trick 7
It's a lot easier game when you can see all 52 cards, and the real difference between the BIL and experts is that the experts will try to build a picture of how the 52 cards lie.
When you are worrying about everything on the hand, it is far more difficult
